From 4ee4edeb28cbf627fb13487b0ff5e3573444070e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 7 Mar 2026 03:51:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix critical bugs and improvements found in deep transformer
 codebase audit

Critical fixes:
- Fix transport operator einsum in pure_fep_transformer.py: was computing
  exp(phi_child) @ exp(phi_parent) instead of exp(phi_child) @ exp(-phi_parent)
  due to contracting on wrong index ('bnik,bnjk' -> 'bnik,bnkj')
- Fix _init_weights overwriting tied embedding initialization: move weight
  init before tying so embedding's calibrated init_std isn't destroyed
- Fix cluster label corruption in rg_metrics.py: in-place relabeling caused
  label collisions when new indices matched later old labels
- Fix _sigma_to_diag crash for diagonal covariance models (3D tensors)
- Fix dict attribute access error in test_query_variation.py

High-severity fixes:
- Fix redundant triangular solve in _kl_gaussian_torch (use ||L^{-1}x||^2)
- Fix lambda lm_head in standard_transformer.py (use nn.Linear with shared weight)
- Fix division by zero in train_fep.py when all batches are skipped
- Add inf check alongside NaN check in train_fep.py
- Fix evaluate() not restoring model attribute on exception (use try/finally)
- Fix stale phi returned in forward_with_attention and forward_with_rg_tracking
- Standardize checkpoint key to 'model_state_dict' across all save/load paths
- Fix resume_training.py using wrong config keys for attention_lr and output_lr
- Fix pad_token_id=0 silently masking valid GPT-2 token "!" in loss computation
- Remove duplicate config keys in train_publication.py (gauge_group, per_head_kappa, etc.)
- Add weights_only=False to torch.load calls for PyTorch 2.6+ compatibility

Medium-severity fixes:
- Fix post-softmax clamping leaking through causal mask (preserve masked zeros)
- Fix entropy computation inflated by clamped zeros from masked positions
- Fix perplexity overflow in Trainer.validate() (cap at exp(20))
- Fix position.squeeze() failing for max_len=1 (use squeeze(-1))
- Fix in-place embedding weight modification (use .data accessor)
- Fix sys.path in belief_space_viz.py pointing to wrong directory
- Initialize _cross_head_perm attribute unconditionally in model __init__
- Fix byte dataset test expecting 256 instead of correct 257 (256 bytes + PAD)

